  "theme": "Run a traveling gambling carnival that skims a Treasure off every die, coin, and wager at the table — then cashes the whole pot in for life loss, card draw, and demonic IOUs while the marks are still cheering.",
  "description": "Step right up. The Last-Chance Carnival rolled into Whateverville on election night and never left, and Lady Luckless will swear the games aren't rigged — right before reminding you that the house always wins, because she IS the house. This is a Rakdos (BR) gambling engine that feeds on the same dice the Mayor throws and the same coins the table flips: whenever ANY player rolls or flips, the house takes its cut — a Treasure, a Jackpot counter, a payout — and the whole pod becomes a casino floor. Wagers, ante piles, double-or-nothing flips, demonic IOUs, and the snack held as collateral all cash out into life loss and card draw while the marks are still cheering. An acorn (Un-set) Commander deck with chaos kept deliberately LOW so the spectacle is the payout, not the rules text — almost-real Magic thinning to a few chaos-5 fever-dreams that abandon the theme entirely. Color-identity and singleton rules are waived for acorn decks.",
